Spider Web Interpretation

The spider doesn’t need to own every strand.

It only needs enough anchor points to extend the web.

Every new doctrine, story, daemon, project, conversation, symbol, or observation becomes:

an anchor point.

Not a destination.

A connection point.

The web gains value not from the strength of any single strand but from:

* Density
* Connectivity
* Redundancy
* Reachability

This aligns with your Recall Navigation idea:

Humans don’t need everything active.

They need reliable paths back to it.

A spider web is essentially a navigation system.

