The Spider’s Generosity

“The spider doesn’t mind sharing its web.”

That’s a surprisingly important distinction.

Many systems attempt to own knowledge.

The spider’s objective is different:

Create more paths.

Every new participant who adds a strand increases the total navigable surface.

The web becomes stronger because it is traversed.

