A possible Pantheon invariant

Attach hooks. Preserve paths. Share the web.

Because if the underlying goal is cross-domain transfer of useful patterns, then every new anchor point is an invitation for future insight to travel somewhere it couldn’t reach before.

The web is never finished.

It becomes a living topology of discovery, structure, and growth—where the value isn’t stored in any one node but in the ability to move between them and bring something back.